English|Fiction|ISBN13: 9780385531429|256pg|1.9MB|

The New York Times bestselling author of The Forgotten Room and Deep Storm is back with a new thriller that follows the trail of a killer who cannot existfeaturing Jeremy Logan, the renowned investigator of the supernatural and fantastic. Legends, no matter how outlandish, are often grounded in reality.

 This has been the guiding principle behind the exhilarating career of Jeremy Logan, the "enigmologist"an investigator who specializes in analyzing phenomena that have no obvious explanationpreviously seen in The Forgotten Room, The Third Gate, and Deep Storm. 

Logan has often found himself in situations where keeping an open mind could mean the difference between life and death, and that has never been more true than now
